doc.after: Star Wars is an American epic space opera franchise consisting of a film series created by George Lucas The film series has spawned a media franchise outside the film series called the Expanded Universe including books television series computer and video games and comic books These supplements to the film trilogies have resulted in significant development of the series fictional universe These media kept the franchise active in the interim between the film trilogies The franchise portrays a universe which is in a galaxy that is described as far far away It commonly portrays Jedi as a representation of good in conflict with the Sith their evil counterpart Their weapon of choice the lightsaber is commonly recognized in popular culture The fictional universe also contains many themes especially influences of philosophy and religion
